that we can tie back

12:28.458 --> 12:29.833
to upper management.

12:29.833 --> 12:31.458
‐ If we circle back
to the doctors,

12:31.458 --> 12:32.667
we should start with the ones

12:32.667 --> 12:34.875
that we busted
for over‐prescription.

12:34.875 --> 12:38.042
Maybe after a few years
sitting in jail,

12:38.042 --> 12:39.833
they'd be willing
to tell us more.

12:39.833 --> 12:41.042
‐ Oh, yeah.

12:41.042 --> 12:43.250
‐ And I'll reach out
to Jay McCloskey.

12:43.250 --> 12:45.583
‐ Sounds good.

12:45.583 --> 12:47.583
I'm gonna get to it.

12:49.083 --> 12:51.375
Hey.

12:53.542 --> 12:56.208
Happy anniversary.

12:56.208 --> 12:57.500
You said it.

13:03.000 --> 13:06.667
‐ Tonight, we celebrate
OxyContin

13:06.667 --> 13:11.000
passing $1 billion
a year in sales!

13:11.000 --> 13:13.417
Yeah!

13:13.417 --> 13:16.458
